# Dependency Injection (DI)

## Definition

Dependency Injection (DI) is a technique in which the required object (dependency) is provided by the Spring IoC Container instead of being created inside the class.

## Types

- Constructor Injection
- Setter Injection

## Advantages

- Loose Coupling
- Better Maintainability
- Easy Testing
- Reusable Components

## Key Point

Spring implements Inversion of Control (IoC) using Dependency Injection (DI).
